<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BaldwinSterilization     10-06 0182</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Baldwin Sterilization,0188</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mother Sterilized to Get Lenient Sentence</HEAD>
<DATELINE>INDIANAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman who gave her 4-year-old son a fatal
dose of prescription drugs has undergone sterilization in hopes of
receiving a lenient sentence, her attorney says.
   Melody S. Baldwin, 29, was sterilized Tuesday at Wishard
Memorial Hospital, said Michael J. Donahoe.
   ``The primary factor in fashioning the sentence for anyone is
the likelihood of repeat behavior,'' Donahoe said Wednesday. ``I
think we're going to be able to assure the court that nothing like
this will happen again.''
   Superior Court Judge Roy E. Jones had suggested he would be
lenient if she underwent the procedure.
   Baldwin pleaded guilty June 10 to neglect of a dependent and, in
exchange, prosecutors dropped a murder charge. She faces a maximum
sentence of 20 years in prison at sentencing Nov. 9, compared to a
20- to 50-year term for murder.
   She was accused of having ``knowingly administered'' lethal
doses of two psychotropic drugs to her son, Joshua, in 1986.
   Baldwin gave birth to a son Sunday and gave him up for adoption,
Donahoe said.
</TEXT>
