<HEAD>At Least 28 Die as Flatbed Trailer Crashes into Bus</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MAHALLA, Egypt (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A flatbed trailer broke loose from a truck
and crashed head-on into a bus, killing 28 people and injuring 21,
an official said Thursday.
   Taha el-Saafan, chief prosecutor in this town north of Cairo,
said all the casualties were on the bus and that the victims ranged
in age from 5 to 40. The bus driver was among the dead, he said.
   The collision occurred Wednesday on a two-lane rural road.
   The public bus was en route from Kafr el-Sheikh, 95 miles north
of Cairo, to Baltim, a summer resort about 30 miles away, el-Saafan
said.
   As the truck approached from the opposite direction, he said,
its trailer became detached.
   He said the trailer was traveling at about 55 mph when it
barreled into the bus.
   He said the truck driver, Saad Aly, 29, surrendered to police
and was under investigation on a number of charges, including
driving an unsafe vehicle.
