<HEAD>Two Men Flee East Germany In Boat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FLENSBURG, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two East German men used a rubber
dinghy to escape from East Germany and were rescued in heavy seas
off the Baltic coast, police said Thursday.
   West German border police in Flensburg said the men, both 22,
eluded East German patrol boats when they set out Tuesday from the
Baltic city of Wismar. The two were picked up in Danish territorial
waters by a Greek freighter early Wednesday, police said. They were
first taken to Denmark, then to West Germany, officials said.
   More than 332 East Germans have fled to West Germany from East
Germany this year, according to government statistics.
