<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Waldheim     10-06 0174</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Waldheim,0180</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Waldheim To Visit Turkey, Syria and Kuwait</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Kurt Waldheim will stop in
Turkey on his return from state visits in Syria and Kuwait in late
October, the presidential office announced Thursday.
   Waldheim is to leave for Syria on Oct. 27 and continue to Kuwait
on Oct. 31.
   The Austrian president, who plans to visit Turkey on Nov. 2, is
scheduled to meet with Turkish President Kenan Evren and Premier
Turgut Ozal, the Austria Press Agency said. It said Waldheim will
return home Nov.3.
   Waldheim has been shunned by Western governments because of
controversy surrounding his activities during World War II.
Waldheim served as an intelligence officer for the German army in
the Balkans.
   He was a member of a unit that was implicated in war crimes in
Yugoslavia and Greece, but Waldheim has denied any wrongdoing.
   With the exception of a trip to the Vatican, Waldheim has not
visited any other Western state as president. He has made official
visits to Jordan, Pakistan and Saudi Arabia.
</TEXT>
