<HEAD>State Dept. Official Going To Eastern Europe</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Deputy Secretary of State John C. Whitehead
will visit Romania, Poland, Czechoslovakia, Hungary and Bulgaria
from Sunday through Oct. 20, his sixth mission to Eastern Europe.
   He will also stop in Berlin.
   In his talks with the leaders of the communist countries,
Whitehead will stress ``the importance which we attach to the
protection of human rights,'' State Department spokeswoman Phyllis
Oakley said Thursday.
   He also will meet with religious leaders and ``a broad
cross-section of society'' and stop in Brussels on the way home to
brief Western officials, she said.
