<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Brawley-Chronology     10-06 0514</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Brawley-Chronology,0536</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Major Events in the Brawley Case</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Brawley Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a chronology of major events in the case
of Tawana Brawley, the Wappingers Falls teen-ager who claimed she
was abducted and raped by a gang of white men. A grand jury found
her story a fabrication.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>1987</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Nov. 28 _ After disappearing for four days, 15-year-old Tawana
Brawley is found at the apartment complex where her family had
lived. She is in a plastic bag, her body smeared with animal feces
and scrawled with racial slurs. According to her family, the girl
was kidnapped and sexually assaulted.
   Dec. 2 _ Fishkill police Officer Harry Crist Jr. commits
suicide. Although he fits the girl's description of one of her
attackers, prosecutors later say it is unlikely the death is
related to the case.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>1988</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Jan. 26 _ Gov. Mario Cuomo names Attorney General Robert Abrams
special prosecutor in the case, but Brawley advisers the Rev. Al
Sharpton and attorneys C. Vernon Mason and Alton Maddox denounce
the appointment and refuse to cooperate.
   Feb. 10 _ Entertainer Bill Cosby and a magazine publisher offer
a $25,000 reward for information in the case.
   Feb. 29 _ A state grand jury is empaneled to investigate.
   May 24 _ Tawana's mother, Glenda Brawley, on the advice of
Sharpton, Mason and Maddox, defies the state's first attempt to
compel testimony from a family member and refuses to appear before
the grand jury.
   June 6 _ Mrs. Brawley again refuses to testify and is ordered
jailed for 30 days and fined $250.
   June 8 _ Mrs. Brawley takes ``religious sanctuary'' in a New
York City church.
   June 15 _ Former Sharpton aide Perry McKinnon says the Brawley
case is ``a pack of lies'' designed to advance the political agenda
of Sharpton, Mason and Maddox. Sharpton and the lawyers call
McKinnon a liar.
   June 16 _ Abrams says he is investigating the possibility of a
hoax in the case.
   June 20 _ Self-described surveillance expert Samuel McClease
says that on Sharpton's orders, he secretly tape recorded
conversations of Brawley advisers discussing misgivings about the
case. The advisers denounce McClease.
   June 21 _ Federal officials direct McClease to appear before a
federal grand jury looking into the Brawley affair.
   June 25 _ McClease turns blank tapes over to authorities and is
charged with obstruction and perjury.
   Aug. 16 _ The Brawley advisers reaffirm their stand: Miss
Brawley will not obey any subpoena. The subpoena is later rescinded.
   Sept. 21 _ Sharpton confirms reports the Brawleys have moved to
Virginia.
   Sept. 27 _ The New York Times, citing sources, reports the grand
jury has overwhelming evidence Miss Brawley lied.
   Sept. 28 _ Miss Brawley, appearing in Newark, N.J., says: ``I am
not a liar and I am not crazy. I just want justice.'' She refuses
to answer questions.
   Oct. 6 _ Grand jury report is issued, calling Miss Brawley's
story a fabrication; Abrams files charges against Mason and Maddox
with a legal review panel, announces that Sharpton is under
investigation, clears Crist and Pagones.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
