<2ND_LINE>AM-Lebanon-Hostages-Text,0485</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Text of Kidnappers' Communique in Beirut</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Lebanon-Hostages</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   This is the full text of the statement
issued Thursday by the Revolutionary Justice Organization,
threatening the safety of two American hostages, as translated from
Arabic by The Associated Press:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   In the name of the almighty,
   The Revolutionary Justice Organization, watching events in
Lebanon, declares that the destiny of Lebanon has become within the
priorities of our struggle in view of the new imperialist onslaught
aimed at the revolutionary strugglers and turning it into a new
Israel and a North Atlantic Treaty Organization base.
   The chain of events which preceded and followed the presidential
election poses the gravest stage of the conspiracy against Lebanon,
because it is not a circumstantial outcome of a domestic crisis,
but part of a conspiracy by Israel, Iraq and NATO carried out by
the mercenaries of the interior to partition Lebanon as a first
step to turning it into an Israeli satellite and a NATO base for
intrigues against the people of the region and to attack steadfast
Syria and other revolutionary regimes.
   The organization calls attention that those who made Lebanon
reach this stage and put its destiny at stake will not be satisfied
with what they have accomplished. They have graver and more
adventurous plans that will push the whole region to the brink and
widen the scope of the conflict, especially with the rude call for
imperialist intervention under the slogan of internationalization
by a colonial power whose black history is mothering our present
tragedies.
   From its revolutionary and combative stand, the Revolutionary
Justice Organization declares a state of utmost alert and will not
stand handcuffed. It specifies the following priorities:
   1. We call the attention of all free revolutionary strugglers to
the seriousness of what is happening and urge them to be vigilant
and close ranks against an imperialist front plotting a black
future. We urge them to forget ideological differences, because the
destiny of all is imperiled.
   2. We warn the conspirators and their tools that we shall mete
out the just punishment to the conspirators. We shall hit the heads
and nests of intrigues in Lebanon wherever they hide, be it in the
Karantina (headquarters of the main Christian militia, Lebanese
Forces), or Hazmieh (army command) or Bkirki (seat of the Maronite
patriarchate). We shall not be tolerant with the grandsons of the
crusaders. We assure them that domination of Lebanon and its
destiny shall remain illusive dreams from which they will be jolted
by our nearing showdown.
   3. We emphasize to the international conspirators that we shall
use all the cards to thwart these conspiracies, including the card
of the safety of the hostages, which we shall make the backbone of
our confrontation.
   Glory is for the oppressed and immortality for the martyrs.
   The Revolutionary Justice Organization
</TEXT>
