   Richard Land, the newly elected
executive director of the Southern Baptist Christain Life
Commission, supports capital punishment, condemns abortion and
opposes ordination of women.
   These were among requirements laid down by the now dominant
fundamentalist administration in finding a replacement for N. Larry
Baker, who left under pressure in June.
   Land, chosen as his successor, says Scripture clearly indicates
