of the church as an organized body and in the family as a team in
the household.''
   He says the New Testament forbids women's ``ordination to the
ministry or ruling authority.''
   Land, 41, has been vice president of academic affairs at
Criswell College, an arm of First Baptist Church in Dallas, led by
the Rev. W.A. Criswell, a leader of ``Bible inerrancy''
fundamentalists.
   Land says he opposes abortion ``except where the mother's
physical life is in extreme danger'' and ``I firmly belief in
capital punishment as part of the biblically mandated authority of
the civil magistrates.''
