<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BusinessmanCharged     10-06 0420</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Businessman Charged,0432</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Millionaire Businessman Charged as Pedophile</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Note contents may be offensive to some readers.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By SAMUEL MAULL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A millionaire businessman and foundation
president has been charged with sodomizing five Harlem boys after
pretending to take an interest in their welfare, prosecutors said.
   William Barnes Hunt, 51, used his money to ingratiate himself
with the boys' families, District Attorney Robert Morgenthau said
Thursday. Hunt bought food, paid some of their families' bills and
took the boys _ aged 6 to 9 _ to parks and zoos.
   Hunt was arrested Aug. 10 and charged with fondling a 6-year-old
boy he had lured into his car on a Harlem street, Morgenthau said.
He said a neighbor had called police after she saw Hunt invite the
boy into his auto.
   Police searched the car and found a small black Scottie dog,
toys, an instant camera and film. The indictment accused Hunt of
using children in sexual performances after police searched his
car, home and office and found four sexually explicit photographs
of naked young boys.
   The 33-count indictment voted Wednesday charged Hunt with 11
counts of sodomy, 13 counts of sexual abuse and nine counts of
endangering the welfare of a child. The top count, sodomy, is
punishable by up to 25 years in prison.
   State Supreme Court Justice Thomas Galligan set Hunt's bail at
$25,000 and scheduled a hearing for Oct. 19.
   The boys Hunt is charged with sodomizing are being tested for
sexually transmitted diseases, Morgenthau said.
   Morgenthau said none of the parents of the boys knew what Hunt
was up to. He said they thought the defendant was a generous man
offering their children a glimpse of life they would not ordinarily
see.
   Hunt's family put him in an undisclosed Manhattan psychiatric
hospital after his arrest because he said he was going to kill
himself, Morgenthau said.
   The district attorney said Hunt might have been involved with
many more children.
   ``We realized very early on that there was probably more to this
case than a single isolated instance of pedophile activity,'' he
said. He asked that anyone with information about such activity
call his office.
   Hunt, an investment banker, is president of Own Canoe Corp., a
firm that offered counseling to children and teens, and president
of the William Barnes Hunt Foundation, Morgenthau said.
   The defendant graduated from St. Paul's preparatory school in
New Hampshire and from Columbia University. He is a member of the
exclusive Union Club in Manhattan.
</TEXT>
