<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Washington Poll,100</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bush Leads Dukakis in Washington State, Poll Says</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEATTLE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vice President George Bush leads Michael Dukakis
47 percent to 41 percent in Washington state, according to a poll
released Thursday, but the gap between the two candidates was
closed by a nearly six-point margin of error.
   The poll, conducted for KING 5 News by Delta Research, says Bush
leads Dukakis in all geographic regions of the state, including
Seattle, where the margin is 48 percent to 41 percent.
   Between Sept. 30 and Oct. 2, Delta Research polled 300 likely
voters in the Nov. 8 election. The margin of error was plus or
minus 5.8 percent.
