<DATELINE>WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Du Pont Co. is asking 20,000 employees
in its fibers department to share the company's profits and risks
starting in January as part of a three-year experiment that
executives say could become a model for the rest of the company.
   The new plan would tie a portion of employees' pay raises to the
department's earnings, the company said Wednesday.
   The plan, called ``achievement sharing,'' gives employees a
stake in the department's performance.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Unions at Eastern Airlines have reacted angrily
to a report that Texas Air Corp. was discussing the possible sale
of its East Coast air shuttle to developer Donald Trump.
   The pilots union warned Wednesday it would seek a court order to
block any such deal, and the head of the machinists union suggested
his union would do the same.
   According to unidentified sources quoted by the Wall Street
Journal, the price tag on the three-city shuttle was in the range
of $200 million.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eastern Airlines has announced the recall of 300
furloughed flight attendants, which follows the recent layoffs of
more than 3,000 employees to streamline the money-losing carrier's
operations.
   The furloughed flight attendants are being recalled effective
Oct. 21 because of the popularity of a long-term leave of absence
program, Eastern spokesman Robin Matell said Wednesday.
   The program was offered as ``a way of minimizing the impact of
furloughs,'' and more volunteers were attracted than had been
anticipated, Matell said. More than 500 flight attendants took the
leave offer.
