<1ST_LINE>r f AM-IacoccaOil     10-06 0362</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Iacocca Oil,0376</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Chrysler Chairman Pushes Olive Oil, Vinegar, Wine</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BILL STIEG</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lee Iacocca thinks you should change your oil.
   Not the 30-weight in your LeBaron, but the oil in your salad and
your marinara sauce.
   The chairman of Chrysler Corp. was in Macy's on Thursday to
promote Villa Nicola olive oil, vinegar and wine, products of the
Tuscany region of Italy where Iacocca bought an estate in 1984.
   ``You can't get this many people out when you're showing a new
car,'' Iacocca said as about 200 people crowded around a stand in
Macy's gourmet food section for a taste and an autograph.
   Iacocca said his family used to bring olive oil and wine from
his estate to American friends, who eventually said, ``Why don't
you put a label on it and sell some of it?''
   Now, Villa Nicola Ltd. markets extra virgin olive oil, balsamic
and Chianti vinegars and red table wine, all of it produced in the
area around the estate, which is named after his father.
   If the company _ run by his daughter, Lia Nagy, and son-in-law
Ned Hentz _ ever turns a profit, the money will go to the Iacocca
Foundation, which funds diabetes research.
   ``It started as a hobby, it's not going to be a big business,''
Iacocca said. ``The olive oil, I think, is in a class with any
olive oil in the world.''
   The products were first sold in Detroit about a year ago, but
now can be found in speciality grocers in several states, including
New York, New Jersey, Ohio and Illinois.
   The customers who lined up for a look at Iacocca were treated to
food prepared according to the recipes of his mother, Antonietta,
including her marinara sauce, pesto sauce, sticky chicken wings and
cheese steaks.
   A liter of the olive oil sold for $19.75.
   ``I tasted the pesto with oil and it was very good,'' said Renee
Press of Long Island. ``I'm gonna try it, I have to watch my
cholesterol.
   ``Besides, I'm a Chrysler shareholder. I got it at $6 and sold
at $50. So I love him. I'll buy it.''
</TEXT>
